[br]Here's the deal. They want to balance the "fun" with how long things take to do.  The longer things take, the more you play. If encounters and camps are fun because they are easy, you will get bored.  If you can PL yourself to 65 in a week, you are going to get bored with the game and quit.  If it takes you months (years in my case) and you have "just enough fun" to keep you logging back on, then SoE wins.  Nerfs are just an attempt to make us play the way that keeps us on line as long as possible.  Kind of like 38 hour AC camps.  I must be retarded for not quitting after that one...

