                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">Sleppen</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/11/2003&nbsp;: 5:22:56 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">HOWEVER, major changes in gameplay for certain classes, should at least be discussed with the players. I don't mean asking for permission, but getting feedback on possible changes. You can either randomly contact uber players off their guild lists, or /whois lvl ? Necromancer and pick a name. Ask them what their major means of hunting is, what spell line-up they use most often, what spells they NEVER use and maybe ask why. These are all simple customer service related things. I dont see why they do not do this to improve the gameplay. I could be wrong and maybe they do this.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />The message board hotheads will never believe it, but SOE does a lot of those things.  It's been an open secret for years that members of the design team are members of some of the top guilds serverwide.  SOE employees monitor the class message boards from time to time.  In fact, I saw Absor on this board earlier today.<br /><br />I don't envy SOE the task of filtering through all of the static on class message boards and feedback messages to try to identify the actual useful information.  A lot of it gets buried in the "SOE suxxors" rants that plague boards like this.<br /><br />As for getting feedback from the players, I can take a pretty good guess at where SOE is coming from on that one.  A little over two years ago (back when the EQ website still had open message boards), someone from SOE (Absor, I think) solicited comments on class balancing.  The result was a protracted exercise in negativity, SOE bashing, and class envy BS.  Not long after that, SOE closed the EQ message boards.  As far as I can recall, SOE has never again solicited direct input from the playerbase at large.<br /><br />We've had discussions on this board before about ways to open a dialogue with the developers.  I've seen discussions along those lines on several other class boards.  Just about everyone feels that they're being neglected by SOE, and just about every message board has posts about how no one at SOE understands their class.  My sense is that SOE has a lot better grip on how the game works than most people think, and certainly a lot better than any of the message board hotheads.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=611383" target="_blank">Sleppen Slyden, Defiler of Cazic-Thule</a> <br /><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=611457" target="_blank">Serreatus Foestriker, Warlord of Rallos Zek</a></span></font></td>
