                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">Deslegrate</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#000000" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/11/2003&nbsp;: 3:17:15 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I agree that alot of aspects to this game are absolutely messed up.<br /><br />Charming is and was one of them.  Like some people have already mentioned, I'd have to agree maybe they didn't go far enough with the exp nerf on charm.  The resist adjustments don't really matter to enchanters, druids have incredibly long lasting snares + SOW, so they aren't really effected too badly if charm only lasts a minuete for them.   However necros have no way to lower MR on their own, no long lasting snares, no AE stun or quick cast mez.  So out of all the changes done, I'd say necros got hurt.   Not that they can't charm kill before, but its (assuming) alot harder now, or alot less efficient.  This is probably not the case for enchanters or druids (possibly a little longer per kill now, but still as safe as before).<br /><br />The aggro changes are a joke.  They have to be a mistake.  People seem to forget that necros are not group friendly with our spells till much later on.  Even then its only a basic contribution most of the time.<br /><br />Fear changes were uncalled for completely, seeing as it wasn't even viable on mobs 55+, so didnt effect the high end content thats out there at all.  Not to mention it was the entire "efficiency" case for necros and dots (whimpy pets/pet spells).  <br /><br />I agree this is a game.  In order to keep things as they want it, they should be able to make changes.  HOWEVER, major changes in gameplay for certain classes, should at least be discussed with the players.  I don't mean asking for permission, but getting feedback on possible changes.  You can either randomly contact uber players off their guild lists, or /whois lvl ? Necromancer and pick a name.  Ask them what their major means of hunting is, what spell line-up they use most often, what spells they NEVER use and maybe ask why.  These are all simple customer service related things.  I dont see why they do not do this to improve the gameplay.  I could be wrong and maybe they do this.<br /><br />Even heading to the most frequented necromancer board, contacting the moderator and having the MODERATOR ask a set of questions to the board, while moderating the thread heavily.  I mean it is not hard to see that charm needed a fix.  However where they decided the Aggro changes or Fear changes were needed, I have no idea.  All of this could be done very easily, and would both improve support for SoE and the changes they do make (not everyone will agree with all changes, but if NEC X has an AAXP charming in CoD every 30mins, then yes thats a needed change), as well as address the issues that the basic and uber necro's are experiencing.  <br /><br />This is all done relatively easily.  They could do this to every class, and both nerf the currently "Broken" ability's, and make the player base happy by fixing a few minor things or tweaking certain spells.  Not that they should be doing this for all classes each week, but a questionaire like that once a month wouldn't be too much of a time sink for them.  Espeacially with things that are simple to fix, like resist adjustments.  At least with something like this, given to US from THEM, we would at least know they are listening in one way or another to our concerns.  Then we may at least understand where the changes come from, instead of out of thin air.<br /><br />At least thats my thoughts on what SoE should be doing for their customers.  Surely I'm not asking for too much.<br /><br />(The idea that I should have to use 570m every min/min and a half just to keep aggro, is ridiculous. When that 570m does 2200dmg.  I dont see how they figured this or something like it was needed or even justifiable.)<br /><br />-Deslegrate the Dark</span></font></td>
