                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/10/2003&nbsp;: 7:23:55 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Fellow necros-<br /><br />Just wanted to throw my 2 coppers into the ring as far as the 'it's just a game' type statements made by people.<br /><br />In fact, it is just a game.  But does that trivialize it to tic-tac-toe? or clue? or stratego? or whatever game you played as a kid?  Football/baseball/basketball, those are all just 'games' as well arent they?  (Didnt you play a game of baseball as a kid?)  Though people get played millions to play them.<br /><br />Here are two truths I know, I doubt most would argue.<br />1) Humans are social animals by nature.<br />2) You can never have more time.<br /><br />Everyones time here is definetly...finite.  We dont know the amount, but you will never get more of it.  IMO it is the most valuable commodity you have in life.  When I was younger, I often tended to put stuff off, 'I'll do that someday' or 'I can see soandso loved one or friend tomorrow' etc, seemed like I had nothing but time on my hands.<br /><br />That being said, someone like me, who <b>invests</b> my time into a game does want it to be enjoyable.  I'm not uber, I'm not a power gamer.  I had a horrible learning curve.  It took me 90 played days to get to lvl 43 pre-kunark with my first main, a ranger.  Thats 2160 hours alone.  That is a major investment of my time, to have fun.  It was my choice to play of course.  You gatta realize that it is disappointing to see something you worked so long (not hard) at become not-so-fun anymore.  Regardless that its just a game.  People will direct that disappointment at the cause of it, the owners/developers of the game.  After 4 years of building a character, making friends, a community if in a guild, its a big pill to swallow to just walk away.  To tell someone, just walk away from 4 years of friends, fun and work is a lil disrepectful for my tastes.<br /><br />So for me, yes it is just a game.  But I dont think it is good form to over simplify the frustration someone may be feeling about the game due to unforeseen changes.  It is not life.  My religion (God),friends, family and love ones are what really matter to me.  But when my fun gets nerfed, I may freak out.<img src="images/furious.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /> and at the least would be understanding of someone else freaking out and not tell them stuff like stfu, its just a game or leave etc.<br /><br />Its not: do unto others as you would have done unto you....<br />Its: love your neighbor as thyself.<br />The latter speaks volumes to me.<br /><br />I myself see these latest changes as a new challenge.  Figuring out strategys to do things I 'shouldnt' be able to do, is the aspect I like most about the game.  The changes may get 'fixed', they may not.  I'll keep playing until something better comes long most likely.  That was my point of view before this patch.  /cheer those that have posted new ideas and techniques because we're all in the same boat.  Some of us are just more upset than others heh.<br /><br />Safe travels friend,<br /><br /><center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=632618" target="_blank">Deegan E'Lusk</a><br />61 Warlock of Innoruuk<br />Fennin Ro</b><br /><br />"I'm yer huckleberry"</center></span></font></td>
